---
import PolicyPage from '../../components/PolicyPage.astro';
import { getTranslation } from '../../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en';
const title = getTranslation(locale, 'seo.privacy.title');
const description = getTranslation(locale, 'seo.privacy.description');
const canonicalUrl = '/en/privacy';
const updatedAt = '2026-03-09';
---

<PolicyPage
  title={title}
  description={description}
  lang="en"
  canonicalUrl={canonicalUrl}
  pageTitle="Privacy policy"
  updatedAt={updatedAt}
>
  <section>
    <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
    <p>The controller of personal data collected through this website is Ignacio Amat.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Name:</strong> Ignacio Amat</li>
      <li><strong>Business activity:</strong> Freelance web design and development</li>
      <li><strong>Contact channel:</strong> the contact form available on this website.</li>
      <li><strong>Location:</strong> Barcelona, Spain</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. What data may be collected</h2>
    <p>The information processed depends on how you interact with the website.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact form:</strong> name, email, company, indicative budget and message, if you choose to provide them.</li>
      <li><strong>Essential technical data:</strong> minimum information required for security, abuse prevention and basic website operation.</li>
      <li><strong>Optional analytics data:</strong> if you accept analytics cookies, aggregated navigation data may be collected through Google Analytics 4.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Why the data is processed</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To respond to service inquiries or collaboration requests.</li>
      <li>To prepare proposals, quotes or pre-contractual discussions.</li>
      <li>To keep the website secure and functioning correctly.</li>
      <li>To understand aggregated website usage, only when analytics cookies have been accepted.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Your data is not sold and is not used for unsolicited automated marketing.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Legal basis</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Consent:</strong> when you submit the form or accept optional cookies.</li>
      <li><strong>Pre-contractual measures:</strong> when your message relates to a potential service engagement.</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interest:</strong> to protect website security and prevent abuse.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> where information must be retained for tax or legal compliance.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Retention</h2>
    <p>Data is retained only for as long as needed to fulfill the purpose for which it was collected and for any legal retention period that may apply.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Commercial inquiries are kept while the conversation is active or there is a reasonable follow-up need.</li>
      <li>Project-related records may be retained for the legally required period.</li>
      <li>Analytics data is subject to provider settings and only exists if consent was given.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>6. Recipients and third parties</h2>
    <p>Personal data is not disclosed to third parties for their own commercial use. Service providers necessary for hosting, email delivery, forms or meeting scheduling may process data under their own terms and, where applicable, as processors.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>7. Cookies and analytics</h2>
    <p>This website uses essential technical cookies for core functionality. In addition, Google Analytics 4 may only load if you explicitly accept analytics cookies through the consent banner.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Analytics is disabled by default.</li>
      <li>You can accept or reject analytics from the consent banner.</li>
      <li>If accepted, Google may process certain technical data according to its own privacy policy.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
    <p>You may exercise your rights of access, rectification, erasure, objection, restriction and portability through the <a href="/en/contact">contact form</a>. You may also withdraw consent at any time where processing is based on consent.</p>
    <p>If you believe your data is being processed unlawfully, you may lodge a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>9. Updates</h2>
    <p>This policy may be updated to reflect legal, technical or operational changes. The version published on this page is the current one.</p>
  </section>
</PolicyPage>
